  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's a comparative overview of legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States\n- Comprehensive Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA) as primary legislative framework\n- Strict reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Significant criminal and civil penalties\n\n2. European Union\n- Unified regulatory approach through Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- Emphasis on customer due diligence\n- Enhanced transparency requirements\n- Centralized information sharing mechanisms\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (POCA)\n- Robust regulatory framework\n- Strong focus on financial intelligence\n- Comprehensive suspicious transaction reporting\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Traditionally banking secrecy laws\n- Increasingly stringent international compliance\n- Sophisticated due diligence protocols\n- Active cooperation with international investigations\n\n5. Singapore\n- Strict regulatory environment\n- Advanced technological monitoring systems\n- Significant penalties for non-compliance\n- Strong international cooperation\n\n6. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Increasing international alignment\n- Strict capital control mechanisms\n- Growing emphasis on digital transaction monitoring\n\nKey comparative observations:\n- Increasing global convergence\n- Technology-driven enforcement\n- Expanding regulatory scope\n- Enhanced international collaboration\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of these approaches?",
